\end{code}
\begin{code}
S -:> T = forall {i} -> S i -> T i
\end{code}
%endif
%
Morphisms are equal if they map each index to pointwise equal functions.
In the sequel, it will be convenient to abbreviate
|Bwd K -> Set| as |(Cix K)|, for types indexed over scopes.



